<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Tribute to A.P.J. Abdul Kalam</title>

    <style>
        *{
            margin:0;
            padding:0;
            box-sizing:border-box;
        }

        body{
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color:#f4f4f4;
            color:#333;
            line-height:1.6;
        }

        .container{
            max-width:1000px;
            margin:30px auto;
            padding:20px;
            background:white;
            border-radius:10px;
            box-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
        }

        .header{
            text-align:center;
            margin-bottom:30px;
        }

        .header h1{
            font-size:3rem;
            color:#0d47a1;
        }

        .header p{
            font-size:1.2rem;
            color:#666;
        }

        .content{
            display:flex;
            align-items:center;
            justify-content:center;
            gap:30px;
            flex-wrap:wrap;
            margin-bottom:30px;
        }

        .content img{
            width:300px;
            border-radius:10px;
            box-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }

        .quote{
            max-width:400px;
            font-size:1.5rem;
            font-style:italic;
            color:#1565c0;
        }

        .about h2{
            margin-bottom:15px;
            color:#0d47a1;
        }

        .about p{
            text-align:justify;
            font-size:1.1rem;
        }

        footer{
            text-align:center;
            margin-top:20px;
            color:#777;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">

        <div class="header">
            <h1>A.P.J. Abdul Kalam</h1>
            <p>1931 - 2015</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content">
            <img src="images/kalam.jpg" alt="A.P.J. Abdul Kalam">

            <div class="quote">
                "Dream, dream, dream. Dreams transform into thoughts and thoughts result in action."
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about">
            <h2>About Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam</h2>

            <p>
                Dr. Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam was one of India's most respected
                scientists and the 11th President of India. Known as the "Missile Man of India,"
                he played a crucial role in the development of India's missile and space programs.
                Born on October 15, 1931, in Rameswaram, Tamil Nadu, he overcame many challenges
                through hard work and dedication. His contributions to science, technology, and
                education inspired millions of people. Dr. Kalam was admired for his humility,
                vision, and passion for empowering young minds. Even after becoming President,
                he remained a teacher at heart and continued motivating students across the country.
                His life remains a symbol of perseverance, knowledge, and service to the nation.
            </p>
        </div>

        <footer>
            Tribute to the People's President of India
        </footer>

    </div>

</body>
</html>
